      <content><![CDATA[<p>OpenCms scales images if requested and caches scaled versions. We demonstrate how to use the <code>&lt;cms:img&gt;</code>-tag in a formatter to scale images.</p>
<p>Note that this is just one way to scale images. Images may also be scaled, cropped, etc. when inserting them into the content when using appropriate widgets (see the related links). Consult theÂ <a href="%(link0)">descriptions of the ImageGalleryWidget and the VfsImageWidget</a> for such options.</p>]]></content>
    </Overview>
